data.enText: a law that is passed by a parliament, council, etc. and formally written down

data.chText: 法规中有关于惩罚措施的规定。
data.enText: Penalties are laid down in the statute .

data.chText: 1987年通过的法令明文禁止体罚。
data.enText: Corporal punishment was banned by statute in 1987.
a formal rule of an organization or institution

data.chText: 按大学的规章制度，校方无权开除他。
data.enText: Under the statutes of the university they had no power to dismiss him.

simple_means.memory_skill: stat 站，立 + ute → 设立后不动的东西 → 法令

tr: an act passed by a legislative body

value.def: A statute is a rule or law which has been made by a government or other organization and formally written down.

example.ex: The new statute covers the care for, bringing up and protection of children...
example.tran: 新法令涵盖了儿童保育、养育和保护的相关内容。

example.ex: The independence of the judiciary in France is guaranteed by statute.
example.tran: 法国司法部门的独立地位是法律明文规定的。
